race.comment: BACK TO BONDI (10) sat close to the speed when beaten 0.7L over the 1400m trip on debut at Bunbury. He stuck on well there and is expected to be better again with that run under his belt. O'Donnell sticks and he'll be able to be close to the speed from the barrier once more. Can get the job done this time. SYLVA JACK (9) got a long way back over 1500m at Pinjarra last start and can sit much closer this time around. Nottle's 3kg claim comes in handy and now third-up and out to the mile, she can land the knockout blow. VAMPI QUEEN (13) flew home from the back first-up before a 0.4L defeat over 1400m at Bunbury last time out. Pike hops on board in a good push for her chances third-up and a forward showing is on the cards. YOU CAN CALL ME AL (1) missed by 1.5L last start and continues to knock on the door. Won't be far away again. BRADBURY'S MOMENT (7) can go close once again if he gets some luck from the draw.
